# 📐 Project Blueprint & Architectural Constraints: [PROJECT_NAME]

## 🛠️ Mandatory Tech Stack
- **Runtime**: [e.g., Java 17, Node 24]
- **Frontend**: [e.g., Next.js 16, Tailwind 4]
- **Backend**: [e.g., Spring Boot 3.4.6]
- **Database**: [e.g., PostgreSQL 16]

## 🏗️ Infrastructure Constraints
- **Docker Required**: [YES/NO]
- **Orchestration**: [e.g., Docker Compose]
- **CI/CD Pipeline**: [e.g., GitHub Actions]
- **Cloud Provider**: [e.g., AWS, Local Only]

## 🔒 Architectural Guardrails
- **Pattern**: [e.g., Monorepo, Microservices, Layered]
- **Security**: [e.g., JWT, OIDC, RBAC]
- **Forbidden**: [e.g., No Inline CSS, No Plain SQL, No Public S3 Buckets]

## 🚦 Compliance Check
Every AI action must verify against this blueprint. If a proposed change violates a constraint (e.g., adding a library not in the approved stack), it must be flagged as a **BLOCKER**.
